# Phase D IntLLM — pinned lm-evaluation-harness reference.
#
# Every Phase D benchmark (make bench-canonical, make bench-knowledge,
# make bench-baselines) MUST install lm-eval from exactly this ref.
# CI fails if drift is detected between installed version and this file.
#
# Rationale (§6.9 R1): lm-eval-harness has known 0.3→0.4 ARC-E normalization
# drift (see FJQ_PHASE_D_P2_1_GATE.md for evidence on ridger/MMfreeLM-370M).
# Pinning eliminates this class of silent benchmark disagreement between
# IntLLM numbers and replicated baselines.
#
# Install command (copy to docs/REPRODUCIBILITY.md):
#   pip install "lm-evaluation-harness @ git+https://github.com/EleutherAI/lm-evaluation-harness.git@$(cat eval/HARNESS_SHA | grep '^ref:' | cut -d' ' -f2)"
#
# How to update (whenever we adopt a newer lm-eval version):
#   1. Edit `ref:` below to the new tag or full SHA.
#   2. Re-run `make bench-baselines` to confirm every pinned baseline (BitNet,
#      MatMul-Free, SmolLM2, Pythia) still matches its previous delta
#      against paper-reported numbers within ±1.0 absolute.
#   3. Commit with `fix(v31-c-p3.1): bump HARNESS_SHA to <new-ref>`.
#   4. Update paper §4.1 reproducibility footnote + rerun
#      scripts/verify_intllm_tables.py --strict.

repo: EleutherAI/lm-evaluation-harness
ref:  v0.4.11
note: tag pinned (not SHA); a future commit will replace `ref:` with the
      full 40-char SHA once a real benchmark run resolves it in CI.
